						<summary>

						<p>Chōḻa, Rājarāja II(?), 12th year = A.D. 1158.</p>						

						<p>The inscription is mutilated and seems to record a gift of land for offerings to the images Chadira-viḍaṅgadēva and his consort set up in the Tiruvēṅgaivāyil temple by the chief Kulōttuṅgachōḻa-Kiḍārattaraiyar.</p>						

